channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Young woman, 27, died after begging GP to help her 'get enough food to live'
item.description: Aspiring writer Maeve Boothby-O'Neill tragically died at just 27 after begging her GP for help as she battled severe chronic fatigue syndrome which left her unable to eat or drink

item.title: Sharks ‘high on cocaine’ after drugs are being flushed down the loo
item.description: It could be affecting their behaviour making them more aggressive.

item.title: The major red flag health warnings that can appear on your tongue
item.description: Checking your tongue can help find signs for a number of different problems that don't show up anywhere else

item.title: Psychic who envisioned Trump assassination attempt gives his US election prediction
item.description: 'I wasn't expecting this to happen until at least August this year.'

item.title: Miriam Margolyes opens up about health struggles and fears for future
item.description: Blackadder and Call the Midwife star Miriam Margolyes, 83, has opened up about her fears for the future, saying she worries about what is coming

item.title: 14 children end up in hospital after trying ‘adult only’ crisps
item.description: The 'R18' crisps are made using an extract from the ultra-spicy ghost pepper.

item.title: 'Entitled cafe refused to sell me a bagel for petty reason – but I got the last laugh'
item.description: Some eateries can be difficult about adults ordering from the kid's menu with many refusing to serve such a meal. One man who faced such a test has revealed how he was able to get revenge

item.title: Woman describes out of body aura she felt in near-death experience after crash
item.description: 'The experience has allowed me to see the beauty of life.'

item.title: Boyfriend left gobsmacked at stranger's actions towards him in the supermarket
item.description: David Roche, 54, is searching for a kind-hearted woman who came to his rescue at Tesco Extra in Cables Retail Park in Prescot on the weekend - he described her as a 'Godsend'
